						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the rock-cut shrine in the Mēlaikōyil temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 7 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by Madirāntaka (Madhurāntaka) Irukkuvēḷār evidently a member of the family of Koḍumbāḷūr for offering one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
